full_description:

Speaker:: Guido Imperiale

Track: PyData: PyData & Scientific Libraries Stack
The Active Memory Manager is a new experimental feature of Dask which aims to reduce the memory footprint of the cluster, prevent hard to debug out-of-memory issues, and make worker retirement more robust.


Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2022 conference, April 11-13 2022.
https://2022.pycon.de
More details at the conference page: https://2022.pycon.de/program/MZUDYP
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydataberlin
Twitter: https://twitter.com/pyconde
